Disney’s doing what many hoped it would – bringing Star Wars to its popular toys-to-life video game series 
Disney Infinity
. Characters from the now Disney-owned Star Wars universe will appear in Disney Infinity 3.0, which is coming to stores this fall, with a Starter Pack for $64.99.

The Starter Pack has Ahsoka and Anakin from the Clone Wars animated cartoon series, and overall there will be three Star Wars playsets available, including one that covers Episodes I-III, one that spans Episodes IV-VI, and a third and final one coming later in the winter depicting events from The Force Awakens.

Disney’s third major release of Infinity will also offer play sets that feature characters and settings from Inside Out, the upcoming Pixar film, a kart racer that uses a range of Infinity characters, and a new Marvel playset that features Iron Man, Ultron and other things from the new Avengers film.




